Package org.opensextant.giscore.events

Class StyleMap

java.lang.Object
org.opensextant.giscore.events.AbstractObject
org.opensextant.giscore.events.StyleSelector
org.opensextant.giscore.events.StyleMap
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, IGISObject, VisitableGeometry, IDataSerializable
public class StyleMap extends StyleSelector
A StyleMap> maps between two different Styles. Typically a StyleMap element is used to provide separate normal and highlighted styles for a placemark, so that the highlighted version appears when the user mouses over the icon in Google Earth client.

Support referenced styles via URLs as typically used in all generated KML as well as inline Styles.

Author:
DRAND, J.Mathews
